library(ggmap)
## Loading required package: ggplot2
##  Google's Terms of Service: <https://mapsplatform.google.com>
##   Stadia Maps' Terms of Service: <https://stadiamaps.com/terms-of-service/>
##   OpenStreetMap's Tile Usage Policy: <https://operations.osmfoundation.org/policies/tiles/>
##  Please cite ggmap if you use it! Use `citation("ggmap")` for details.
library(ggplot2)
library(sf)
## Linking to GEOS 3.11.2, GDAL 3.8.2, PROJ 9.3.1; sf_use_s2() is TRUE
key = 'e7f97169-8de3-4e18-9683-5e08ee8affa3'
register_stadiamaps(key)
# Load the 2018 SQF data
SQF = read.csv('C:/Users/labuser/Desktop/sqf-2018.csv')

# This will fix the coordinates of the SQF locations!
SQF_force = st_as_sf(SQF, coords = c('STOP_LOCATION_X', 'STOP_LOCATION_Y'), crs = 6539, remove = FALSE)
SQF_force = st_transform(SQF_force, crs = 'WGS84')
# Make a basic map of NYC
bbox = c(
  bottom = 40.46970080525381,
  top = 40.97089384857539,
  left = -74.34002391221547,
  right = -73.65542422393432
)

map = ggmap(get_stadiamap(maptype = 'alidade_smooth', bbox = bbox, zoom = 10)) +
  theme() +
  labs(title = 'your title')
##   Stadia Maps  Stamen Design  OpenMapTiles  OpenStreetMap contributors.
map

# Now easy to plot the SQF events as points - inherit.aes = FALSE is the critical argument
map +
  geom_sf(data = SQF_force, size = 0.5, alpha = 0.2, inherit.aes = FALSE)
## Coordinate system already present. Adding new coordinate system, which will
## replace the existing one.

# Load the community district data, and convert to lat/lon coordinates
CB = st_read('C:/Users/labuser/Desktop/nycd_23d/nycd_23d/nycd.shp')
## Reading layer `nycd' from data source 
##   `C:\Users\labuser\Desktop\nycd_23d\nycd_23d\nycd.shp' using driver `ESRI Shapefile'
## Simple feature collection with 71 features and 3 fields
## Geometry type: MULTIPOLYGON
## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: 913175.1 ymin: 120128.4 xmax: 1067383 ymax: 272844.3
## Projected CRS: NAD83 / New York Long Island (ftUS)
CB = st_transform(CB, crs = 'WGS84')
# This will count up how many SQF events are in each community district
ovlp = st_contains(CB, SQF_force) # finds the SQF events contained in each comm dist
cts = lapply(ovlp, length) # counts up the number of SQF in each comm dist
cts = unlist(cts) # gets the counts out of an R 'list' and into a normal vector
CB$cts = cts # assign that vector to a new column in CB
head(CB, n = 10)
